# Bartender SOP

  [bold]1.[/bold] The bartender must ensure that no uncovered and unattended drinks are left on the bar counter;

  [bold]2.[/bold] The Bartender is permitted to use their shotgun on unruly bar patrons in order to throw them out if they are being disruptive. They are [bold]not[/bold], however, permitted to apply lethal, or near-lethal force;

  [bold]3.[/bold] The Bartender is exempt from legal ramifications when dutifully removing unruly (ie, overtly hostile) patrons from the Bar, provided, of course, they followed Guideline 1;

  [bold]4.[/bold] The Bartender is not permitted to possess regular (ie, lethal) shotgun ammunition. Only beanbag slugs are permitted. Exception is made during station ending emergencies;

  [bold]5.[/bold] The Bartender has full permission to forcefully throw out anyone who climbs over the bar counter without permission, up to and including personnel who may have access to the side windoor. They are not, however, permitted to do so if the person in question uses the door, or is on an active investigation.
